fvwm-themes-0.7.1 - not released yet

* New transparent theme.
* A new function for removing all bindings on a given
  window (see the FAQ)

fvwm-themes-0.7.0 - 20031031

* New full-featured theme RedmondXP.
* New themes: Sa, PlainBow, CelticBow, E17, Ice, QNX.
* Improvements in several existing themes.
* Better backgrounds for several existing themes.
* New set of nice backgrounds in background@underground.
* Added graphical colorset viewer/info (Shift-Ctrl-F8).
* German and Polish translations.
* Debian packages.

fvwm-themes-0.6.2 - 20021206

* Fixes for perl-5.8.0 and a unicode locale (RedHat 8.0).
* File names are now compatible with Solaris's pkgmk.
* Included 48x48-infox icon set (was 48x48-general) for normal icons.
* Added support for wheel mouse in settings.
* Several improvements including better mini icons and more bindings.
* Now the packages are called fvwm-themes and fvwm-themes-extra.
* This is probably the last version for fvwm-2.4.x.

fvwm-themes-0.6.1 - 20020619

* Now installable in Cygwin.
* The Themes Center GUI is much faster.
* Fixed installation when fvwm-config is not in $PATH.
* Added background@ and window border tile to Metal theme.
* Added autogenerated menus of popular headlines on the web.
* Included 16x16-kde icon set (was 16x16-general) for menu and mini icons.

fvwm-themes-0.6.0 - 20011025

* Improvements in the theme switching.
* The Themes Center GUI is much faster now.
* Added ewmh and ksmserver support.
* Added Xinerama support (see the faq).
* Added Debian menu system support.
* New themes: Metal, Minimal (in extra).
* And much more...

fvwm-themes-0.5.0 - 20010810

* The package is now divided to fvwm-themes-base and fvwm-themes-extra.
* Theme names are now shown in mixed case (Default, CDE).
* New themes: BrushedMetal, nanoGUI, Mech, Unsafe.
* New titlebar button order selector, see buttons@multichoice and @nanogui.
* Component menus-user@ renamed to menus-programs@, you should "Reset all".
* New component colors-decor@, may be used to define only a part of colors@.
* New component fonts@, may be used to control fonts using filter functions.
* Added font variants for several euro-asian charsets in fonts@multichoice.
* Components or variants not supported by the user's system are hidden.
* Improvements in several themes, especially Default and OSX.

fvwm-themes-0.4.2 - 20010329

* converted all icons to a new extended wm-icons-0.3 list
* several Solaris and FreeBSD related fixes
* improved @redmond98, press-able buttons and gradient titles
* some work on a minimal reload (optional); reload is now a bit faster
* improvements in documentation and menus

fvwm-themes-0.4.1 - 20001220

* initial KDE version 2 support
* background improvements in @default and @migo
* added modular i18n; more languages may be easily added now
* Some progress for BSD's and Solaris support
* Fixed fvwm-themes-images png icons transformation
* A font selector

fvwm-themes-0.4.0 - 20001111

* fixes, improvements and documentation

fvwm-themes-0.3.21 - 20001103

* completed cde theme
* new GUI started - Configuration Center
* new FvwmScript-ColorSelector
* added some more global bindings
* small fixes and improvements

fvwm-themes-0.3.20 - 20001004

* Themes Center can manage FVWM Themes' sessions and "settings"
* Themes Center supports french and russian locales
* added modules@luthien
* a possibility to use Restart on theme switching (see FAQ)
* fixed a freeze of XFree-4.0.1

fvwm-themes-0.3.19 - 20000917

* added an initial theme luthien from Dominik Vogt
* components now can be locked (i.e. not affected by load [all])
* nicer welcome message and some more small enhancements

fvwm-themes-0.3.18 - 20000907

* added pixmap cursors in @multichoice
* several bug fixes and improvements

fvwm-themes-0.3.17 - 20000828

* new default background
* more Amusements and Games menu entries
* several bug fixes and improvements

fvwm-themes-0.3.16 - 20000819 (cvs)

* A GUI Theme Selector: FvwmScript-ThemesCenter.
* FVWM Themes has now its own session concept (fvwm-themes-start).
* Re-added a support for gnome-session and other session managers.

fvwm-themes-0.3.15 - 20000807 (cvs)

